g.title: j1793214914
g.text: Hey Eleanor? You remember that board game Amir is putting together? Fables & Frontiers?

g.title: j2180075044
g.text: Hey Eleanor? You and Amir are friendly, right?

g.title: j2014158562
g.text: Yes. The one you said was going to be a waste of time, and that you were only playing out of pity for him, that's the one, isn't it?

g.title: j1940139276
g.text: He's a charming little imp. Why are you asking?

g.title: j1264540541
g.text: As much as the next person, I suppose. Why are you asking?

g.title: j147225297
g.text: Yikes. Okay. you're still mad. Noted.

g.title: j3545305061
g.text: I figured you were "too cool for it" at the time, and I was just trying to pretend I was, too. Now I know better.

g.title: j1282914717
g.text: Yeah I... I just wanted to say sorry about that, I... didn't mean what I said about it. I was just scared you'd say no.

g.title: j3550416937
g.text: Amir's trying to get the team together to play a game of Fables & Frontiers, and I said I'd help.

g.title: j405363061
g.text: Amir really wants to play Fables & Frontiers with everybody. You in?

g.title: j2529622265
g.text: Which one of us is no longer "too cool" for the game, exactly? You or I?

g.title: j3153027766
g.text: We've all been there at one point in our lives... trying to wear a mask to impress someone and falling flat on our face because we can't see where we're going. And you and I had barely met when you asked. All right. You're forgiven.

g.title: j1354720372
g.text: Ah. I see. You are the chosen messenger, sent from the Thunderbolt King to enlist fair Eleanor. No doubt all sorts of roguery await me. Fol de rol and so forth.

g.title: j881321496
g.text: You. I still think it's a dorky game, but whatever.

g.title: j887505389
g.text: Me. Definitely me. You're still too cool for the game. But I'm an utter dweeb, or so Quincy says.

g.title: j2280877005
g.text: Honestly, putting on a daft voice and play-acting for a few hours sounds ideal. Count me in.

g.title: j1694534357
g.text: I think it'll be fun, honestly. And it seems to mean a lot to him.

g.title: j2498418658
g.text: Yeah, I think it's going to be a total waste of time, but I'm trying to be nice.

g.title: j958604635
g.text: Oh! I would like to be a wizard. Or perhaps a bard. Or perhaps both? Can you BE both?

g.title: j1143420798
g.text: I will do you a favour and NOT convey those words along to him. Word to the wise: treat him with more respect in the future in my presence.

g.title: j890629738
g.text: Or I could be a swamp hag! So long as I get to wear a tight bodice, mind. Mother Mossytits will eat your bones, little manikin.
